2. Freeze a human-readable capsule

Produce one archival file that explains the system in simple text and includes hashes of the core artefacts.

tools/codex_capsule.py

from __future__ import annotations
import pathlib, json, datetime, hashlib

ROOT = pathlib.Path(".")
OUT = ROOT / "codex_capsule.txt"

def sha(p: pathlib.Path) -> str:
    h = hashlib.sha256()
    if p.is_file():
        h.update(p.read_bytes())
    else:
        for f in sorted(p.rglob("*")):
            if f.is_file():
                h.update(f.relative_to(ROOT).as_posix().encode())
                h.update(hashlib.sha256(f.read_bytes()).digest())
    return h.hexdigest()

def main():
    capsule = {
        "timestamp": datetime.datetime.utcnow().isoformat()+"Z",
        "description": "Human-readable summary of the Codex project.",
        "core_hashes": {
            "omega_lock": sha(ROOT/"OMEGA_LOCK.json"),
            "charter": sha(ROOT/"CODEX_CHARTER.md"),
            "license": sha(ROOT/"LICENSE.txt"),
            "economy": sha(ROOT/"economy_monetization.json")
        }
    }
    text = (
        f"CODEX CAPSULE â€” {capsule['timestamp']}\n"
        "This document records the essential fingerprints of the Codex project.\n\n"
        + json.dumps(capsule, indent=2)
    )
    OUT.write_text(text, encoding="utf-8")
    print("ðŸ“¦ Codex capsule created:", OUT)

if __name__=="__main__":
    main()

This gives any future reader a single file that can prove authenticity even if every other service disappears.


---

3. Establish a succession key

Generate a public/private key pair (offline) and publish only the public key in your repo:

PUBLIC_STEWARDSHIP_KEY.asc

-----BEGIN PGP PUBLIC KEY BLOCK-----
(Comment: Codex Stewardship Key)
...
-----END PGP PUBLIC KEY BLOCK-----

Keep the private key offline.
This lets future maintainers sign their own Omega locks and keeps the lineage verifiable.


